cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.CR

This paper deals with natural language processing techniques to classify different categories of online harassment in social media. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper also addresses challenges in labeling these categories, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). The paper also discusses the concept of sexism, which could be related to cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
